Honoring the Cardington Volunteer Fire Department on
its Sesquicentennial.
WHEREAS, The members of the House of Representatives of the 136th 1
General Assembly of Ohio are pleased to extend special recognition to 2
the Cardington Volunteer Fire Department on the memorable occasion of 3
its One Hundred Fiftieth Anniversary, celebrated September 7, 2024; 4
and 5
WHEREAS, All those associated with the Cardington Volunteer Fire 6
Department have played a valuable role in community safety. Willingly 7
giving of their time, energy, and abilities far beyond what is 8
required or expected, these fine individuals have fulfilled their 9
responsibilities with the utmost efficiency and effectiveness, and 10
their professionalism, positive work attitude, and cooperation with 11
the public have earned them the esteem and appreciation of the 12
citizens they have so ably protected; and 13
WHEREAS, The Cardington Volunteer Fire Department is truly 14
deserving of high praise, for since it was established in 1874, it has 15
set a fine example of professional deportment and proactive engagement 16
with the community. We are pleased to note that it is through the 17
efforts of organizations such as this that our state continues to grow 18
and prosper and remains responsive to the diverse needs of its 19
residents; and 20
WHEREAS, Countless citizens in the community owe their safety, and 21
some their very lives, to the members of the Cardington Volunteer Fire 22
Department. Indeed, these exemplary first responders have displayed an 23
unwavering dedication to excellence, facing each situation with 24
tremendous courage and presence of mind, and those individuals 25
pursuing a career in the fire service could find no better example to 26

